git-branch

-r/--remotes
  List or delete(if used with -d) the remote-tracking branches.

-a/--all
  List both remote-tracking branches and local branches.

--list
  Activate the list mode.

-D
   Delete a branch irrespective of its merged status

-m/--move/-M
   Move/rename a branch

--set-upstream-to=<upstream>/-u <upstream>
 Set up <branchname> a tracking information so <upstream> is considered
 <branchname>s upstream branch. If no <branchname> is specified, then it
 defaults to the current branch.

--contains <commit>
 Only list branches which contain the specified commit.Implies --list.

---merged <commit>
 Only list branches whose tips are reachable from specified commit.

--no-merged <commit>
 Only list branches whose tips are not reachable from specifed commit

<start-point>
 The new branch head will point to this commit. It may be given as a
 branch name, a commit-id, or a tag. If this option is ommited, the
 current HEAD will be used instead.
